			<div id="contentright">
				<h1>What's this?</h1>
				<p>A whole region terrain editor for <a href="http://secondlife.com">Second Life</a>.<br />Check on some <a href="screenshot.html">screen shots</a>.</p>
				<h1>Tell me more.</h1>
				<p>If you own a private island in Second Life, you can download a region's terrain as a file.  Backhoe reads those files and gives you the tools to terra-form the entire region at once.  Later, you can upload the edited file back to Second Life and your whole region will be changed.</p>
				<h1>How do I get it?</h1>
				<p>It's free.  Just download from the links at left.  Also, it's open source.  You can get the source code and recompile it if you want.</p>
				
				<h1>What do I need to run it?</h1>
				<p>A Macintosh running Mac OS X 10.4 or later.</p>
				
				<h1>How about a manual?</h1>
				<p>The application includes help, though admittedly paltry at this point.  You can read it on-line: <a href="help.html" target="_blank">Backhoe Help</a>.</p>
			</div>
